        },
        {
            "text": "where 1/\u03ba and 1/\u03b3 are the latent and infectious periods, respectively.",
            "cite_spans": [],
            "ref_spans": [],
            "section": "Estimation of the reproduction number"
        },
        {
            "text": "Given M incidence measurements, y data i , at time points, t i , separated by \u2206t (i = 1, ..., M ), the best fit exponential rise r is determined by minimizing the Poisson negative log likelihood [5] :",
